Welcome to Sift!

Is it difficult for you to understand how to recycle your trash correctly? If you are curious to learn the solution to this problem, we have it for you.

“Approximately every square mile of ocean has more than 46,000 pieces of plastic floating in it.”
- Who said it

What is Sift?
Sift is a mobile application where the users can scan items and learn how and where they can recycle them. Sift can also help users find the nearest recycling facilities based on their location.
Problem
Whenever we do not know how to recycle our trash we put it in the general bin.
Solution
With Sift you will be able to know how
to recycle items correctly.
Features
Sift is an educational waste management mobile application that helps users make informed recycling decisions through locating convenient recycling centres, filtering search functions and allowing for further education with an object scanning and depositing feature.
Scan Objects
You can scan an object with your camera, the application can identify different materials and will tell you how to recycle them correctly.
Find Recycling Centers
Local recycling centers can be found near you, where you can bring items that can't be easily disposed of.
Search by Item Name
You can scan an object with your camera, the application can identify different materials and will tell you how to recycle them correctly.
